SB167 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to the Alabama Administrative Procedure Act;
5 to amend Section 41-22-20, Code of Alabama 1975; to revise the
6 standard of judicial review of agency rulings.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
8 Section 1. Section 41-22-20 of the Code of Alabama
9 1975, is amended to read as follows:
10 "§41-22-20
11 (a) A person who has exhausted all administrative
12 remedies available within the agency, other than rehearing,
13 and who is aggrieved by a final decision in a contested case
14 is entitled to judicial review under this chapter. A
15 preliminary, procedural, or intermediate agency action or
16 ruling is immediately reviewable if review of the final agency
17 decision would not provide an adequate remedy.
18 (b) All proceedings for review may be instituted by
19 filing of notice of appeal or review and a cost bond with the
20 agency to cover the reasonable costs of preparing the
21 transcript of the proceeding under review, unless waived by
22 the agency or the court on a showing of substantial hardship.
23 A petition shall be filed either in the Circuit Court of
24 Montgomery County or in the circuit court of the county in
25 which the agency maintains its headquarters, or unless
26 otherwise specifically provided by statute, in the circuit
27 court of the county where a party other than an intervenor,
28 resides, or if a party, other than an intervenor, is a
Page 1

resides, or if a party, other than an intervenor, is a
